    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 1000 SERIES - REPLACEMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REPLACEMENT</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CLUTCH PEDAL SHAFT BUSHING</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the clutch pedal return spring (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1100503">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the clutch pedal from the upper clutch rod by removing the cotter and clevis
                    pins.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the brake pedal return spring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the brake pedal from the brake cylinder rod.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pedal shaft bolt lock nut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pedal shaft bolt, clutch pedal (with bushings), brake pedal (with bushings)
                    and spacer tube from the steering column support bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1100503" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100503" filename="../figg11/G1100503.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Clutch Pedal Shaft Details</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BRAKE PEDAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BUSHING (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPACER TUBE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CLUTCH PEDAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. STEERING COLUMN SUPPORT BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. PEDAL SHAFT BOLT, LOCK NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. RETURN SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. PEDAL RETURN STOP</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. PEDAL PAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. PEDAL TRAVEL STOP</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. CLEVIS PIN, COTTER PIN (NOT SHOWN)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discard the old bushings. Inspect the spacer tube and bores of the pedals for wear.
                    Replace if worn or damaged. Replace clevis pins if worn.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the inside and outside diameters of the new bushings with a light coat of
                    grease. Use 251H EP grease or an equivalent NLGI #2 multi-purpose lithium grease.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the spacer tube and bushings in the bores of the pedals.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the clutch pedal (with bushings), brake pedal (with bushings) and spacer tube
                    into the steering column support bracket and install the pedal shaft bolt and lock nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the pedal shaft lock nut to 75 to 85 ft-lbs. (102 to 115 N&#8226;m). Be sure the
                    pedals pivot freely after tightening lock nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the brake pedal to the brake cylinder rod. Adjust brake free travel if
                    necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the brake pedal to the return spring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the clutch pedal to the upper clutch rod and install a new cotter pin. Lubricate
                    the clevis pin with a light coat of grease.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the clutch pedal return spring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the clutch control adjustments and readjust as needed. Refer to to
                    <hotlnk document="s11005r_4.xml" xrefid="hl1100501">ADJUSTMENT
                        <xref refid="hl1100501"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
